@yujuhong I suggest we keep consistent within a runtime? 
As the pod level interfaces are created for pod-level runtimes like rkt. The implementation path we took for docker is just because it lacks "pod", there's no way to figure out whether a dead container belongs to an "older" pod or an "older than older" pod. That's why we have more containers in a pod returned by GetPods() than the pod spec for docker. 

On the other hand, rkt already has the pod concept, it's looks like a backfire if we choose the docker path for this kind of interface when integrating rkt.

